Nonbreeding.description: Nonbreeding Tufted Puffins have rounder heads and larger, thicker, more orange bills than Rhinoceros Auklets. They usually have pale markings on the head, echoing the yellow tufts of breeding plumage.

Breeding.description: Breeding Tufted Puffins are black with white faces and extravagant yellow plumes sweeping behind the head, unlike the Rhinoceros Auklet's overall grayish color.
Cassin's Auklets are smaller than Rhinoceros Auklets, with a shorter neck and smaller, all-dark bill.
Crested Auklets are smaller than Rhinoceros Auklets and have only one white streak on the face. Crested's bill is shorter and brighter orange than Rhinoceros.
